<subSubSection id="5CEF6559AB52FFEDFF7EFD16FACEFD63" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="144A36D2AB52FFEDFF7EFD16FACEFD63" blockId="28.[151,1437,153,1223]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="2681EAC0AB52FFEDFF7EFD16FEDEFD5F" bold="true" box="[199,334,693,719]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="D3F54D51AB52FFEDFD85FD16FD17FD5F" authorityName="Weglarz &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2020" box="[572,647,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herkos">
<emphasis id="2681EAC0AB52FFEDFD85FD16FD17FD5F" box="[572,647,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">herkos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the Greek noun, meaning fence or wall. This name was chosen because the dorsolateral processes of the pygofer are reminiscent of a wall. The noun is in the genitive singular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5CEF6559AB52FFEDFF7EFD5EFCD7FC5B" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="144A36D2AB52FFEDFF7EFD5EFCD7FC5B" blockId="28.[151,1437,153,1223]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="2681EAC0AB52FFEDFF7EFD5EFEABFC87" bold="true" box="[199,315,765,791]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is easily distinguished from the rest of 
<taxonomicName id="D3F54D51AB52FFEDFC20FD5EFB89FC87" authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1971" box="[921,1049,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2681EAC0AB52FFEDFC20FD5EFB89FC87" box="[921,1049,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Chionomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the dorsolateral projections of the pygofer. These projections combined with point of origin of the processes on segment X indicate that this species may be allied with 
<taxonomicName id="D3F54D51AB52FFEDFE1AFCE6FDA5FCCF" authorityName="Weglarz &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Muir" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[419,565,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dissipatus">
<emphasis id="2681EAC0AB52FFEDFE1AFCE6FDA5FCCF" box="[419,565,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. dissipatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D3F54D51AB52FFEDFDFAFCE6FD7FFCCF" authorityName="Weglarz &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Muir" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[579,751,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gluciophilus">
<emphasis id="2681EAC0AB52FFEDFDFAFCE6FD7FFCCF" box="[579,751,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. gluciophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis id="2681EAC0AB52FFEDFC97FCE6FC67FCCF" box="[814,1015,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="D3F54D51AB52FFEDFC97FCE6FC63FCCF" box="[814,1011,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripinosus">C. quadripinosus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
All three of these species have slight dorsolateral expansions of the pygofer however none are as prominently produced. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="D3F54D51AB52FFEDFB59FCCAFADCFC13" authorityName="Weglarz &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2020" box="[1248,1356,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herkos">
<emphasis id="2681EAC0AB52FFEDFB59FCCAFADCFC13" box="[1248,1356,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. herkos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from these species in having a rounded armature of the diaphragm as opposed to having it toothed and quadrate (
<taxonomicName id="D3F54D51AB52FFEDFA3AFC2EFE97FC5B" authorityName="Weglarz &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Muir" baseAuthorityYear="1926" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dissipatus">
<emphasis id="2681EAC0AB52FFEDFA3AFC2EFE97FC5B" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. dissipatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D3F54D51AB52FFEDFEACFC12FE50FC5B" authorityName="Weglarz &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Muir" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[277,448,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gluciophilus">
<emphasis id="2681EAC0AB52FFEDFEACFC12FE50FC5B" box="[277,448,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. gluciophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or U-shaped (
<taxonomicName id="D3F54D51AB52FFEDFDD2FC12FCA6FC5B" authorityName="Weglarz &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Muir &amp; Giffard" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[619,822,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Chionomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrispinosus">
<emphasis id="2681EAC0AB52FFEDFDD2FC12FCA6FC5B" box="[619,822,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. quadrispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
